SIMPLE: underling
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Underling
<hw>Un"der*ling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Under</ets>
+ <ets>-ling</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An inferior person or agent;
a subordinate; a low-ranking employee.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence,</specif> <def>A mean, sorry fellow.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The fault, dear Brutus, is not in our stars,⟦br⟧
But in ourselves, that we are <qex>underlings</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Underlip</ent>⟦br⟧
